        "node": {
            "id": "cG9zdDoxMjk0",
            "title": "SQL Joins: What They Are and How To Use Them",
            "slug": "sql-joins-what-they-are-and-how-to-use-them",
            "date": "2023-11-27T17:33:50",
            "modified": "2024-07-10T20:11:37",
            "featuredImage": null,
            "excerpt": "<p>SQL joins are functions that consolidate data from multiple tables based on a specified condition, typically involving a primary key in one table and a foreign key in another. Joins return subsets of the original tables that meet the provided conditions, creating new combinations of rows. Types of joins include inner joins, left and right outer joins, full outer joins, and cross joins, each offering different results based on their unique logic and join conditions.</p>\n",
            "categories": {
